ct has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it is no longer available. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.</em>","My Pattern Designer understands that standard sizing in the textile industry can be anything but standard. The <a href=\"/best-embroidery-software\">software</a> includes a collection of patterns designed for women’s clothing. The standard package includes 30 of the company’s most popular patterns, including dresses, blouses, trousers and outerwear, with a credit for one free pattern of the buyer’s choice.","Standard sizes can vary even on the same body. When sizing for a pattern using this program, you begin by choosing a body type. Next, you select an upper body size and a lower body size. Height and fullness are chosen from a range of Tall/Plus, Standard or Petite/Slim, to help you zero in on the exact size.","In case that level of control over sizing is insufficient, My Pattern Designer includes a sizing wizard that creates a size from the five most common dress measurements: height, bust, waist, hip and inseam. The wizard program takes that information and measures it against upper and lower body measurements from the American National Standards Institute. The best matches are merged together, including adjustments made for height and leg length, to create the closest size match for the pattern. Beyond that, there is a menu from which to select specific areas that might not fit a standard size, such as a fuller bust or skinnier legs. My Pattern Designer allows you to save as many customized measurement sets as you need, eliminating the need of inputting the same information with every new pattern.","The patterns included in the standard package provide options for hems, seam allowances, facings, line color and width, and more. Lengths can be fully adjusted, and darts and pleats added. The patterns include seven basic sleeves and 20 advanced sleeves, and five choices of collar. Tools to create princess line, yoke, closure, and vent and insert adjustments are all included as well. There are even tools for accessories to tie the look together.","The website, although its appearance seems a little outdated, is packed with information regarding patterns, directions, video demonstrations and customer testimonials. A customer service email is provided, and a Get Help link contains FAQs and other resources to help ensure that any problems are solved in short order. The price for the standard edition is reasonable for the amount of control it gives you. It may not be the flashiest pattern-making program, but it will get the job done, and done well."]},"id":"02e27121-7363-4e29-9622-5a9bcdf47d21","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_61207","url":"/my-pattern-designer-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"top-ten-reviews-contributor","url":"/author/top-ten-reviews-contributor","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Top Ten Reviews Contributor","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"w5zRTt8zKNM8ERYhxFTX9","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-11-18T17:05:24Z","datePublished":"2014-11-18T17:05:24Z","name":"My Pattern Designer Standard","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it is no longer available.","review":{"pros":[""],"cons":[""]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it is no longer available.","language":"en","dateModified":"2014-11-18T17:05:24Z","id":"6L6sUNfLaXatSSvTTfqcaU","meta":{"title":"My Pattern Designer Standard Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"A garment-design program built around extensive customization to create patterns for people of all shapes. Read more here."},"products":[{"slug":"my-pattern-designer-standard","url":"/product/my-pattern-designer-standard","dateCreated":"2